image_analysis.description: A high-angle, wide shot of a building's exterior entrance. The building is constructed from light-colored stone blocks. Centered is a large, arched double wooden door with a circular window at the top and a hanging lantern. To the left and right of the door are tall, narrow windows with black metal security bars. Two trees frame the shot on the left and right sides. There are small signs and a brass plaque on the wall near the door.
image_analysis.layout: Symmetrical architectural composition featuring a central doorway flanked by windows and trees.

stamps_or_markings.description: Bates stamp or document identifier at bottom right: EFTA00000002
Red security warning sign on the left door/gate area
Small red sign and brass plaque to the right of the main door

notes: The text on the red signs and the brass plaque is mostly illegible due to distance and lighting, except for the surveillance warning which is partially readable based on standard signage patterns.
